View Task

Task Header

Task header contains the following information:

  1. Priority - the priority of the task. Can be Low, Medium, High
  2. State - current Task state
  3. Type - type of the task
  4. Assignee of the task

Task page

 

Once the Task is opened, the Task details page is displayed. In the Task details page you can find following information:

  1. Task Details - displays the basic task information
  2. Related Persons - the assignee of the task
  3. Related Content - displays all documents, cultural objects, samples etc. related to the task
  4. Sub tasks  - displays the tasks related to the current one
  5. Related Persons  - the assignee of the task
  6. Related Comments - displays all comments on the task and on the content created within the task

To access more detailed information select from following tabs:

  1. Details
  2. System Data
  3. Permissions
  4. Versions
